tions allow direct comparison between works such as Guitar, Head of a Woman Fernande and several mid career bronzes. The curators arranged these objects to show shifting surfaces and the ways light reads across torn cardboard and hammered metal. The display makes technical differences audible by letting textures command attention alongside composition and gesture while showing how borrowing, reuse and improvisation sit at the heart of Picasso practice</p>"}'}], 'model': 'gpt-5-mini'}}
