2026-01-05 20:39:27,839 DEBUG openai._base_client: Request options: {'method': 'post', 'url': '/chat/completions', 'files': None, 'idempotency_key': 'stainless-python-retry-8b26dc4f-1393-48c3-a4b6-a87592741f99', 'json_data': {'messages': [{'role': 'user', 'content': 'Translate the following tourist description to fr, ensuring that its inviting and descriptive tone is maintained. Keep all HTML tags intact and return only the translated text.\n{"text":"<p>Gathers canvases and watercolours to track how Turner responded to the rise of the industrial city. The sequence opens with Thames views that show barges, bridges and early steam craft, then moves to later canvases where weather, smoke and motion become pictorial subjects. Specific works include Rain Steam and Speed, The Fighting Temeraire, and The Burning of the Houses of Lords and Commons which anchor the thematic arc.</p><p>One highlight is Rain Steam and Speed where the train carriage becomes both subject and pictorial device. Two don\'t miss pieces are a watercolour study of a fogbound river and a small oil sketch that maps how Turner simplified forms into light fields. Those studies make the decision making behind the large canvases visible and show how the artist used quick sketches as building blocks.</p><p>The show pays attention to urban infrastructure by bringing in architectural drawings, contemporary prints of new bridges and period maps. A hidden gem is a pencilled itinerary that notes river crossings and times which helps explain Turners obsession with particular vantage points. Labels also point out colour recipes and pigment choices so the technical process reads alongside the visual drama.</p><p>Exhibition design uses low shelving and strategic lighting to let watery surfaces and smudged washes breathe. Loans from regional collections allow side by side comparison of early and late Thames views. The narrative emphasises change and adaptation as Turner absorbs industrial technology into a long practice of maritime painting and atmospheric study</p>"}'}], 'model': 'gpt-5-mini'}}
