2026-01-05 20:44:52,235 DEBUG openai._base_client: Request options: {'method': 'post', 'url': '/chat/completions', 'files': None, 'idempotency_key': 'stainless-python-retry-27b4b87c-a84c-4b38-9794-766e1a71bf48', 'json_data': {'messages': [{'role': 'user', 'content': 'Translate the following tourist description to fr, ensuring that its inviting and descriptive tone is maintained. Keep all HTML tags intact and return only the translated text.\n{"text":"<p>Presents Gordon Matta Clark work that turned buildings into sites of artistic incision and social experiment. The layout interleaves site photographs, architectural plans and reconstructed fragments so the cuts read as both material acts and social commentary. Key items include documentation of Splitting, Conical Intersect and Office Baroque alongside measured drawings and trial models.</p><p>One highlight is the photographic sequence of Splitting which records the careful planning and ultimate physical division of a suburban house. Two don\'t miss elements are a scale model of Conical Intersect that reveals how a circular void reshapes interior light, and a set of original construction sketches that show subcontractor instructions and margin notes. Those items underline the mix of conceptual audacity and practical negotiation behind each intervention.</p><p>The display broadened the context by including contemporary responses from architects and urbanists who discuss reuse, vacancy and community reclamation. A hidden gem is a set of annotated film stills where Matta Clark frames ordinary domestic details as sculptural elements. Labels point to the legal and logistic implications of cutting up buildings and to the politics of urban redevelopment at the time.</p><p>Activity materials reproduce pages of permits and letters so the administrative afterlife of the cuts becomes visible. The exhibition also stages a small reconstruction of a removed wall so it is possible to stand in a scaled version of a cut and feel how space reorients around absence. The overall emphasis rests on how physical intervention can interrupt assumptions about property and utility</p>"}'}], 'model': 'gpt-5-mini'}}
