2026-01-05 20:51:03,859 DEBUG openai._base_client: Request options: {'method': 'post', 'url': '/chat/completions', 'files': None, 'idempotency_key': 'stainless-python-retry-6e0ccab1-c60d-46c8-805a-e1e38aed3bfe', 'json_data': {'messages': [{'role': 'user', 'content': 'Translate the following tourist description to ru, ensuring that its inviting and descriptive tone is maintained. Keep all HTML tags intact and return only the translated text.\n{"text":"<p>Brings together recent work by women artists who use painting, sculpture and installation to test form and social expectation. The selection includes works by Tracey Emin, Mona Hatoum and Njideka Akunyili Crosby alongside new commissions by early career makers. Specific pieces cited include a new large scale textile installation, an intimate portrait oil, and a mixed media sculpture that reworks domestic objects.</p><p>One highlight is a commissioned immersive work that folds fabric and light into a walkable room. Two don\'t miss elements are a sequence of portrait paintings that operate at small scale yet reward close looking, and a series of sculptural assemblages that refashion household items into formal statements. Those works make the curatorial argument that material choice and scale can both unsettle and clarify content.</p><p>The exhibition pairs historical contexts with recent practice by showing archival letters and printed manifestos beside contemporary outputs. A hidden gem is a photocopied zine from the nineties found in a private donation which traces informal networks of exchange. Labels outline technical processes such as fabric dyeing, casting and print transfer so the making process stands alongside formal readings.</p><p>Public programmes schedule artist talks and practical sessions that open out technical methods used in the galleries. The display foregrounds material evidence of labour and shows how artists repair, adapt and magnify ordinary objects. Placement across rooms aims to let smaller works breathe while giving large installations the space to register physically</p>"}'}], 'model': 'gpt-5-mini'}}
