2026-01-05 20:54:45,183 DEBUG openai._base_client: Request options: {'method': 'post', 'url': '/chat/completions', 'files': None, 'idempotency_key': 'stainless-python-retry-60bfa41a-a4d8-4fac-9d93-ad702645aec4', 'json_data': {'messages': [{'role': 'user', 'content': 'Translate the following tourist description to it, ensuring that its inviting and descriptive tone is maintained. Keep all HTML tags intact and return only the translated text.\n{"text":"<p>Collects specimens and objects that illuminate life in the deep ocean together with the technology used to find it. The layout moves from shallow continental shelves to hydrothermal vents, bringing in preserved fish, a giant squid arm, and intact tube worms from vent chimneys. Specific items include a glass preserved giant squid arm, a collection of bioluminescent fish specimens, and a remote operated vehicle camera loop that records living behaviour.</p><p>One highlight is a large articulated assemblage that reconstructs a deep sea animal from museum samples side by side with modern photographic evidence. Two don\'t miss elements are the ROV camera loop that shows animals swimming in real time and an interactive table that explains pressure and temperature gradients found at depth. Those elements aim to make physical conditions understandable through hands on demonstration and film.</p><p>The display attends to human technology as much as to biology by showing early bathyscape models, modern submersible suits and sampling equipment. A hidden gem is an annotated logbook from a mid century expedition that records field notes and sketches of unknown organisms. Panels discuss conservation issues and how sampling methods have changed, and there is a lab area that explains specimen preservation techniques.</p><p>Lighting design mimics ocean depth by dimming gallery light as the route progresses. The programme includes specialist talks from marine scientists who address taxonomy and new discoveries. The show places an emphasis on field technique and the many ways knowledge accumulates in cabinets and behind laboratory doors</p>"}'}], 'model': 'gpt-5-mini'}}
