2026-01-05 21:02:07,114 DEBUG openai._base_client: Request options: {'method': 'post', 'url': '/chat/completions', 'files': None, 'idempotency_key': 'stainless-python-retry-6deaaa67-852f-46cc-9eeb-14abccaebf8d', 'json_data': {'messages': [{'role': 'user', 'content': 'Translate the following tourist description to fr, ensuring that its inviting and descriptive tone is maintained. Keep all HTML tags intact and return only the translated text.\n{"text":"<p>Maps recent shifts in portrait practice where identity, performance and digital art meet older studio conventions. The galleries place staged photography, painted reworkings and digital portraits alongside historical reference images to show how artists respond to lineage. Specific works include a large scale photographic portrait by Kehinde Wiley, a staged self portrait by Cindy Sherman, and a small oil painting by Lucian Freud on loan from a private collection.</p><p>One highlight is a sequence of painted reworkings that take canonical poses and reassign gender or cultural markers. Two don\'t miss items are a photographic diptych that uses pattern and costume to unsettle scale, and a video portrait where sound and image shift with the subject movement. Those pieces emphasise how portraiture now interrogates performance as much as likeness.</p><p>The curators include technical notes on retouching, composite photography and paint handling so it is possible to read method alongside meaning. A hidden gem sits in the prints cabinet where a set of preparatory sketches reveals how composition developed across media. Display panels also discuss legal and ethical debates that surround photographic practice and post production.</p><p>Programming pairs gallery talks with practical portrait sessions using analogue photography and life drawing. The layout keeps smaller works in intimate rooms and places large format photography on deeper walls so scale and gaze become active factors in perception. The overall approach records a field in which portraiture keeps renewing its own conventions</p>"}'}], 'model': 'gpt-5-mini'}}
