2026-01-05 21:12:27,131 DEBUG openai._base_client: Request options: {'method': 'post', 'url': '/chat/completions', 'files': None, 'idempotency_key': 'stainless-python-retry-43b643a8-d006-47d7-93b9-8d0172ea83e8', 'json_data': {'messages': [{'role': 'user', 'content': 'Translate the following tourist description to ru, ensuring that its inviting and descriptive tone is maintained. Keep all HTML tags intact and return only the translated text.\n{"text":"<p>Collects recent photographic projects that push the scale and method of the medium. The galleries juxtapose staged tableaux large scale prints and multi screen installations to show how photographers negotiate truth and artifice. Specific names included in the sweep are Nan Goldin, Wolfgang Tillmans and Cindy Sherman with representative works such as staged portrait series and immersive print installations.</p><p>One highlight is a panoramic city study printed at gallery scale that compresses multiple viewpoints. Two don\'t miss elements are a series of candid street photographs compiled over a decade and a staged self portrait series that reworks costume and gesture. Those works show the range from documentary accumulation to rigorous production in contemporary photography practice.</p><p>Curators include technical notes on printing processes and discuss pigment choices, file resolution and paper types so the material process becomes legible. A hidden gem is a small notebook with contact sheets and annotations that records decisions about cropping and sequencing. The show arranges modular displays so small prints get close looking space and large works retain viewing room.</p><p>Programme events include artist led walk throughs and practical masterclasses in analogue darkroom technique. The layout addresses how scale alters perception and how the same image can read differently when printed large or shown on screen</p>"}'}], 'model': 'gpt-5-mini'}}
