2026-01-05 21:17:07,141 DEBUG openai._base_client: Request options: {'method': 'post', 'url': '/chat/completions', 'files': None, 'idempotency_key': 'stainless-python-retry-d54ff792-6ef5-49b3-8b32-44038f0a6694', 'json_data': {'messages': [{'role': 'user', 'content': 'Translate the following tourist description to ru, ensuring that its inviting and descriptive tone is maintained. Keep all HTML tags intact and return only the translated text.\n{"text":"<p>Examines contemporary responses to urban change with installations drawings and small scale models that ask how density mobility and landscape interact. The show brings together architects artists and urban researchers. Specific items include a scale model of a proposed mixed use block, an installation that tracks pedestrian flows, and a photographic series that records informal markets across different districts.</p><p>One highlight is a room sized model that visitors can circumnavigate to see shifting shadows and wind studies. Two don\'t miss elements are a set of commissioned films by local makers that play short narratives about neighbourhood change and a mapping installation that overlays transport data with demographic shifts. Those items make large systems legible through objects and moving image.</p><p>The curators pair speculative architectural drawings with found objects salvaged from redevelopment sites to show the material consequences of urban planning choices. A hidden gem is a set of transcribed oral histories kept in the archive that give first hand accounts of small scale adaptations to major projects. Labels discuss participatory design experiments and the limits of large scale interventions.</p><p>Public programming includes workshops on tactical urbanism and drop in sessions with planning researchers. The arrangement emphasises material thinking and shows how models plans and stories assemble into different versions of future urban life</p>"}'}], 'model': 'gpt-5-mini'}}
